00:51.760 --> 00:54.471
<i>♪ Everything I want ♪</i>

00:54.554 --> 00:57.682
<i>♪ Comes at a cost ♪</i>

00:58.141 --> 01:00.769
<i>♪ And I want ♪</i>

01:01.186 --> 01:02.812
<i>♪ It all ♪</i>

01:09.527 --> 01:12.280
<i>♪ So ring me up ♪</i>

01:12.906 --> 01:14.783
<i>♪ Put it on my tab ♪</i>

01:16.201 --> 01:19.037
<i>♪ Whatever the cost ♪</i>

01:19.370 --> 01:21.790
<i>♪ I'm good for it ♪</i>

01:22.749 --> 01:25.126
<i>♪ So ring me up ♪</i>

01:25.877 --> 01:28.588
<i>♪ Put it on my tab ♪</i>

01:29.380 --> 01:32.383
<i>♪ Whatever the cost ♪</i>

01:32.467 --> 01:34.969
<i>♪ I'm good for it ♪</i>

01:35.970 --> 01:38.765
<i>♪ So ring me up ♪</i>

01:39.224 --> 01:41.559
<i>♪ Put it on my tab ♪</i>

01:42.769 --> 01:45.814
<i>♪ Whatever the cost ♪</i>

01:46.064 --> 01:48.483
<i>♪ I'm good for it ♪</i>

01:55.115 --> 01:59.786
<i>♪ If I leave you tomorrow... ♪</i>

02:00.829 --> 02:02.914
[girl] Daddy, look at me!

02:03.498 --> 02:07.293
<i>♪ Would you still remember me? ♪</i>

02:09.963 --> 02:11.506
[Mitch] Get down in the knees.

02:12.882 --> 02:14.384
Single-double jump combo.

02:17.637 --> 02:19.180
[panting]

02:19.264 --> 02:20.390
Double-single-double?

02:26.646 --> 02:27.480
[Mitch] Good.

02:27.814 --> 02:28.982
That's how it's done.

02:29.440 --> 02:30.859
[Carol] Good morning.

02:32.485 --> 02:33.862
-Hey.
-[Mitch] Thanks.

02:34.279 --> 02:35.196
Yeah.

02:35.280 --> 02:36.406
She's doing well.

02:36.489 --> 02:37.574
Well, show me.

02:37.657 --> 02:38.783
[music through headphones]

02:39.284 --> 02:40.451
You ready to pick out fabrics?

02:40.535 --> 02:43.204
I was thinking something fun and bright
for your costume this year.

02:43.288 --> 02:46.291
[music volume increases]

02:48.877 --> 02:49.711
Can we just--

02:49.794 --> 02:52.422
Yeah, sure. Let's... [clears throat]
Just keep going.

02:53.006 --> 02:54.757
[sighs]

02:56.676 --> 02:57.510
[Mitch clears throat]

02:57.594 --> 02:59.012
-Carol, I--
-Before you say anything,

02:59.095 --> 03:01.264
I just want to say that, um, I know...

03:02.182 --> 03:05.560
we crossed a line, and I'm sorry.

03:05.643 --> 03:08.396
You know, it was completely
out of character for me.

03:08.938 --> 03:09.772
Uh...

03:10.148 --> 03:12.025
Maybe not completely,
but because of the drinks--

03:12.108 --> 03:13.151
Hey! Whoa!

03:13.234 --> 03:15.695
I was just gonna say
how much I like your hair.

03:17.614 --> 03:19.324
-Very David Bowie.
-[laughs]

03:21.826 --> 03:23.244
-Thanks.
-I had a good time.

03:23.870 --> 03:24.871
I promise.

03:25.872 --> 03:29.709
I thought we could go for drinks again.
Only that this time, remember to eat

03:29.792 --> 03:31.836
so that we don't
embarrass ourselves again.

03:31.920 --> 03:33.004
[laughs]

03:34.047 --> 03:35.006
Okay.

03:35.089 --> 03:35.924
Yeah.

03:36.966 --> 03:38.384
[sighs]

03:40.136 --> 03:41.262
Ooh, you're bleeding.

03:41.763 --> 03:43.097
Oh, uh, no. It's--

03:43.181 --> 03:44.724
It's just, um, a hangnail.

03:44.807 --> 03:45.767
I'll just--

03:53.274 --> 03:55.026
[Mandy] They passed their senior test,

03:55.109 --> 03:56.903
but Regionals is a whole new level.

03:56.986 --> 03:59.447
I really want their spins
to have an impact on the judges,

03:59.530 --> 04:02.033
so anything you can do
with the costumes to help.

04:03.534 --> 04:05.245
All right. Come on out, kids.

04:07.497 --> 04:09.999
[Mandy] Oh, my God! You look like angels.

04:11.542 --> 04:12.543
[Justin] Wow.

04:12.627 --> 04:15.338
We look like we're getting ready
for the <i>Hunger Games</i> tribute parade.

04:15.421 --> 04:16.714
Wait. No!

04:16.798 --> 04:18.049
They're perfect.

04:18.549 --> 04:20.301
Dad, help me out?

04:20.385 --> 04:22.804
Listen to the ladies, son.
They always know best.

04:23.304 --> 04:24.722
[Justin sighs]

04:24.806 --> 04:25.807
[Mandy] All right.

04:26.307 --> 04:29.435
Let's remove the sparkle from his,
tighten up the sleeves,

04:29.519 --> 04:31.688
maybe move the neckline up a little bit.

04:32.397 --> 04:34.440
And as for Kat's,

04:35.483 --> 04:36.901
don't change a thing.

04:37.777 --> 04:40.196
Oh, my goodness.
I didn't realize it was so late.

04:40.280 --> 04:43.157
Honey, did you remember to bring
the welcome flyers for the conference?

04:43.241 --> 04:44.534
Crap, I forgot 'em.

04:44.617 --> 04:47.120
I'd go get 'em myself,
but I have a meeting in 20 minutes.

04:47.203 --> 04:48.079
It's fine.

04:48.162 --> 04:50.123
Justin, could you run home
and grab 'em real quick?

04:50.206 --> 04:51.666
Don't you guys have people for that?

04:51.749 --> 04:53.084
Yeah, you.

04:53.751 --> 04:55.295
-[cell phone buzzing]
-Shit.

04:55.795 --> 04:57.005
Listen, I gotta take this call.

04:57.463 --> 04:58.381
[James] I'm leaving.

04:58.464 --> 04:59.799
-[James] I'll see you later.
-Okay.

04:59.882 --> 05:00.800
[James] Hello?

05:04.137 --> 05:05.388
You look perfect.

05:14.272 --> 05:15.106
Mom?

05:22.322 --> 05:23.406
[Mandy] Are you okay?

05:26.075 --> 05:27.118
Yeah.

05:27.201 --> 05:28.036
It's fine.

05:29.287 --> 05:31.331
She usually makes my costumes,

05:31.414 --> 05:34.208
so it's probably just a little weird
for her.

05:35.460 --> 05:37.295
Anyway, what's my share?

05:37.378 --> 05:40.256
Oh, don't be silly.
James and I are taking care of it.

05:40.715 --> 05:41.924
Thanks,

05:42.008 --> 05:45.178
but when I said I wanted to pay my half,
I meant for everything.

05:46.471 --> 05:48.306
My mom didn't think I could do this.

05:48.890 --> 05:51.017
-I need to show her I can.
-[Mandy] Okay, then.

05:51.100 --> 05:52.560
Your half will be 700.

05:52.643 --> 05:54.604
-[scoffs] Dollars?
-Hm-mm.

05:55.229 --> 05:58.524
Sure. That's fine.
I'll have it for you tomorrow.

05:58.608 --> 05:59.484
Okay.

06:17.668 --> 06:18.836
Hi, could you help me?

06:22.215 --> 06:23.341
Hey, could you help?

06:23.424 --> 06:24.258
Oh!

06:25.510 --> 06:26.636
Okay, cool.

06:27.845 --> 06:29.722
[man] Ugh, two minutes!

06:30.348 --> 06:32.975
I can't remember the last time
someone hit that. That's Olympic pace!

06:33.059 --> 06:36.813
No way, man! I'd have to shave at least
ten seconds off to sniff the podium.

06:36.896 --> 06:37.730
[man] Whatever!

06:37.814 --> 06:39.899
-You're giving me a run for my money.
-[laughs]

06:39.982 --> 06:42.693
[inhales] Starting to wish I didn't
ask you to join the team anymore.

06:42.777 --> 06:44.570
[laughter]

06:45.071 --> 06:47.657
[laughs weakly] Yeah.
Look, I'll catch you guys later.

06:48.074 --> 06:51.285
I gotta head back to Jimmy's.
You know I'm a working man, unlike you.

06:51.369 --> 06:54.705
Hey, dude. I hope you know I'm just
busting your balls. You're kicking ass.

06:54.789 --> 06:55.998
Oh, yeah, man.

06:56.082 --> 06:57.542
[Marcus] It's all good. [laughs]

07:01.295 --> 07:02.296
Oh! Oh!

07:02.380 --> 07:04.257
Let me help you with this. [laughs]

07:06.467 --> 07:08.010
-[Marcus] There you go.
-Thank you.

07:08.094 --> 07:09.178
Of course.

07:09.262 --> 07:11.305
All these people,
and it's like I'm invisible.

07:11.389 --> 07:12.598
[woman laughs]

07:12.682 --> 07:14.434
-I'm Alana.
-Marcus.

07:17.854 --> 07:20.314
Uh... So, how long
have you been working here?

07:20.398 --> 07:21.482
Just started.

07:22.024 --> 07:24.318
Uh, just needed some extra help
to get me out of CDI.

07:25.611 --> 07:27.905
It's a small community college
not too far from here.

07:27.989 --> 07:29.157
Oh, cool.

07:29.699 --> 07:31.117
Yeah. [chuckles]

07:31.200 --> 07:34.954
I can't lie, I almost broke my neck
when I saw a black guy on the ski team.

07:35.037 --> 07:37.415
[laughs] Yeah, it's white as snow here.

07:37.498 --> 07:38.541
Yeah.

07:38.624 --> 07:40.793
But it's cool, you know.
You get used to it.

07:40.877 --> 07:42.211
[men laughing]

07:42.295 --> 07:46.174
Just make sure you have your camera ready
when these guys get drunk later

07:46.257 --> 07:49.343
and try and dance at the conference,
like conga line and shit.

07:49.427 --> 07:50.970
-[Marcus] You'll never forget it.
-Okay.

07:51.053 --> 07:52.597
You actually won't be able to forget it.

07:52.680 --> 07:54.265
-[Alana] Okay!
-[both laughing]

07:54.348 --> 07:55.349
I'll see you around.

07:55.433 --> 07:56.434
All right. You too.

08:01.063 --> 08:01.981
[Jenn] <i>Nope.</i>

08:02.440 --> 08:03.357
No way!

08:04.650 --> 08:06.652
That one. Perfect for Leah.

08:06.736 --> 08:08.738
[Gabe laughs]
It's like a peacock ate another peacock

08:08.821 --> 08:10.031
and then puked it up.

08:10.114 --> 08:13.367
It just might be busy enough to distract
from how much of a bitch she is.

08:13.451 --> 08:14.535
Come on. She's not that bad.

08:14.619 --> 08:16.787
Plus, I think we finally have a shot
at beating Justin,

08:17.246 --> 08:18.956
so I'm trying to be a fan of hers.

08:20.249 --> 08:21.876
[Gabe gasps] Speak of the devil!

08:22.585 --> 08:25.213
I got over my liking-my-straight-friends
phase a long time ago,

08:25.296 --> 08:28.382
but I will never deny how hot he is!

08:29.008 --> 08:29.884
[Jenn] He's okay.

08:30.259 --> 08:33.804
Stop it. Nobody would ever describe
Justin Davis as "okay."

08:33.888 --> 08:35.348
You'd totally bone him.

08:37.058 --> 08:38.768
[gasps] I have the best idea!

08:38.851 --> 08:40.269
We're going out tonight.

08:40.353 --> 08:41.312
Go invite him.

08:41.395 --> 08:42.730
-No way.
-Go.

08:42.813 --> 08:44.357
-No.
-Fly, little bird.

08:44.440 --> 08:45.608
-No!
-Then I'm doing it.

08:46.859 --> 08:48.569
I hate you so much right now.

08:49.820 --> 08:50.863
Justin?

08:51.697 --> 08:55.952
Uh, me and Gabe are getting shitty tonight
at Grayson's Alehouse if you wanna come.

08:56.410 --> 08:57.370
Cool. I'll try.

08:57.912 --> 08:58.746
[Gabe] Bye!

09:00.915 --> 09:02.458
Oh, my God! He's so into you.

09:02.542 --> 09:03.543
[Jenn] No!

09:03.626 --> 09:05.002
[Gabe] Okay. Here we go.

09:05.086 --> 09:06.420
[Jenn] Let's move.

09:10.341 --> 09:14.428
Well, thanks. I will be sure to reach out
if I ever think of buying a house there.

09:14.512 --> 09:17.390
And I will be your roommate.

09:17.473 --> 09:18.432
[laughter]

09:19.934 --> 09:22.228
Uh, company card. Enjoy.

09:27.525 --> 09:28.568
Holy shit!

09:29.735 --> 09:31.779
He gave me a $120 tip.

09:31.862 --> 09:33.573
That, with the money I have saved up,

09:33.656 --> 09:36.951
means I can pay my half
for the skating costume.

09:37.034 --> 09:40.621
I can pay the choreographer.
I can pay the coach, my ice time.

09:41.330 --> 09:42.999
My mom's just gonna have to live
another day

09:43.082 --> 09:45.668
knowing her daughter's actually doing
this skating thing on her own,

09:45.751 --> 09:46.627
thank you very much.

09:47.044 --> 09:47.878
Cool.

09:48.754 --> 09:50.881
Hey, look, what's up
with these one-word answers?

09:50.965 --> 09:52.300
Am I missing something?

09:53.551 --> 09:55.761
You texted me
that you were with your sister.

09:56.262 --> 09:57.179
I was.

09:57.263 --> 09:58.848
And then I saw you skating with Justin.

09:59.682 --> 10:00.516
What do you think--

10:00.600 --> 10:02.268
I just don't wanna chase after
a lost cause.

10:02.351 --> 10:04.312
There's nothing going on with Justin.

10:05.271 --> 10:07.523
I <i>was </i>with my sister when I texted you.

10:08.316 --> 10:12.028
Look, what you saw
was just a last-minute practice.

10:12.111 --> 10:13.112
I promise.

10:13.779 --> 10:14.614
[Kat] Hey...

10:15.406 --> 10:18.284
give me another chance, okay?
We can go out tonight?

10:18.868 --> 10:21.329
We'll talk about anything but Justin.

10:22.997 --> 10:27.293
Well, I mean, there is this
arts walk thing I was gonna go to.

10:27.877 --> 10:29.462
Really? Me too.

10:31.005 --> 10:32.298
Call it a date?

10:32.923 --> 10:34.383
I work the split-shift.

10:34.467 --> 10:35.760
I could meet you after.

10:36.135 --> 10:37.637
I gotta go to the bank and get changed,

10:37.720 --> 10:39.555
so I'll meet you in the lobby
when you're done?

10:39.972 --> 10:40.931
Cool.

10:41.599 --> 10:42.600
Cool.

10:47.563 --> 10:51.901
[thumping music]

10:58.824 --> 11:00.826
["Raise Your Solo Cup" playing]

11:06.624 --> 11:08.459
Hey! Knock it off!

11:09.210 --> 11:10.503
Idiots!

11:10.586 --> 11:12.630
Hey, have you guys seen
a big, blue box anywhere?

11:12.713 --> 11:14.048
[Justin] I guess Dad left it here.

11:14.131 --> 11:15.341
Ask him yourself, idiot.

11:15.424 --> 11:16.592
[Drew] He can't, idiot.

11:16.676 --> 11:19.345
Dad's at the doctor with Mandy
getting the ultrasound.

11:22.723 --> 11:23.849
Mandy's pregnant?

11:23.933 --> 11:25.226
You weren't supposed to say that.

11:25.810 --> 11:28.104
Sorry. Dad was gonna tell you
at the family dinner tomorrow.

11:30.815 --> 11:31.649
[inhales]

11:31.732 --> 11:33.567
Why should I give a shit?
Nothing to do with me.

11:34.694 --> 11:36.362
Thank you, Margie. Appreciate it.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.496
-[cashier] Next.
-[Kat] Hey.

11:45.579 --> 11:51.001
I'd like to deposit this cash
and get a money order for $700, please.

11:51.836 --> 11:54.296
[keyboard tapping]

11:56.090 --> 11:58.968
I'm sorry, you don't have enough money
in your account for the money order.

11:59.635 --> 12:00.845
No, I--

12:00.928 --> 12:03.931
I have $1,586.19.

12:04.014 --> 12:06.726
I keep track of everything.
Can you just check it again?

12:06.809 --> 12:09.729
I understand that, Miss,
but you have no money in your account.

12:11.605 --> 12:12.857
That's not possible.

12:14.483 --> 12:16.986
Wait. It says here
that the co-owner of the account

12:17.069 --> 12:18.696
made a withdrawal earlier today,

12:18.779 --> 12:20.197
a Carol Baker.

12:24.452 --> 12:25.453
[Carol] <i>Anything you want.</i>

12:25.536 --> 12:29.081
Anything.<i> </i>Well, up to $1,586,
but that's enough, right?

12:29.915 --> 12:31.167
[Serena] Wait. Seriously?

12:32.251 --> 12:35.379
-Mom, where'd you get that much money?
<i>-</i>Well, I have savings, sweetheart.

12:35.463 --> 12:38.090
Plus, no expense is too much
for my favorite daughter.

12:38.174 --> 12:39.175
[sniffs]

12:39.258 --> 12:41.302
Oh, come on!
That deserves a smile, at least.

12:41.385 --> 12:42.720
What's up with you lately?

12:43.888 --> 12:45.598
Mitch is my coach, Mom.

12:47.099 --> 12:49.310
I know that.
What's that have to do with anything?

12:49.393 --> 12:52.605
Harley's cousin saw you guys wasted,

12:52.688 --> 12:55.941
hanging all over each other
at some random bar the other night.

12:57.276 --> 12:58.986
I want you to stop seeing him.

12:59.069 --> 13:01.614
My dating life is none of your business!

13:01.697 --> 13:03.491
I deserve to be happy!

13:03.574 --> 13:07.077
So why don't you just check your attitude
and let me buy you a fucking dress?

13:10.331 --> 13:11.165
This is nice.

13:25.054 --> 13:27.556
I can't believe
you actually stole from me.

13:29.350 --> 13:32.311
-You took everything out of my account.
-<i>Your </i>bank account?

13:32.394 --> 13:33.687
It's <i>our </i>bank account, okay?

13:33.771 --> 13:35.606
And let's not even talk about
who owes who here.

13:35.689 --> 13:38.651
I paid for you for 18 years.
Frankly, this is a drop in the bucket.

13:38.734 --> 13:39.860
Bullshit!

13:39.944 --> 13:43.072
That was <i>my </i>money.
I've worked for months to save that up.

13:43.155 --> 13:44.532
Oh, God! Always so dramatic.

13:45.032 --> 13:46.367
I closed the account.

13:46.450 --> 13:47.910
Just stay out of my life.

13:49.036 --> 13:51.330
-[sighs]
-[footsteps retreating]

13:53.332 --> 13:54.208
Pretty.

13:57.002 --> 13:58.045
Is it true?

13:59.129 --> 14:02.716
Of course not, okay? Kat's just mad
that she's not gonna be the only one

14:02.800 --> 14:04.426
getting a new competition dress.

14:06.470 --> 14:08.514
You're on my side, right, honey?

14:13.143 --> 14:16.355
I know how hard it is for you
to handle Kat sometimes,

14:18.566 --> 14:20.150
especially since you're bipolar.

14:22.486 --> 14:23.654
Oh, hi, Mitch.

14:27.908 --> 14:29.243
Why did you do that?

14:44.091 --> 14:45.676
Can you let Mandy know I brought this by?

14:45.759 --> 14:47.303
Of course, Mr. Davis.

14:48.512 --> 14:49.722
She's actually right here.

14:49.805 --> 14:51.473
[Mandy] Oh, great. You found them.

14:51.557 --> 14:53.058
Thank you so much, Justin.

14:53.142 --> 14:56.270
Alana, could you go ahead
and get those flyers out for me, please?

14:56.729 --> 14:59.607
Honey, don't forget
you're on your own for dinner tonight.

15:00.524 --> 15:01.817
[James] Hey, you heard the lady.

15:01.901 --> 15:03.986
What do you say we go into town
and get us some steaks?

15:04.069 --> 15:06.113
You couldn't just tell me earlier,
face-to-face?

15:07.531 --> 15:08.616
What are you talking about?

15:08.699 --> 15:11.744
I had to find out from my little brothers
that you and Mandy are having a kid.

15:12.620 --> 15:13.454
Justin, I--

15:13.537 --> 15:15.873
It's fine that you don't give a shit
about what I think.

15:16.248 --> 15:18.167
The thing that really sucks is that...

15:18.709 --> 15:21.170
I'm the only one
that still seems to remember Mom.

15:23.005 --> 15:24.590
This has nothing to do with your mother.

15:25.007 --> 15:26.508
Yeah. Gotta go.

15:35.225 --> 15:36.268
-There you go.
-Thanks.

15:38.312 --> 15:40.522
-Ah, you again.
-[laughs]

15:40.606 --> 15:42.107
You're not getting tired of me?

15:42.191 --> 15:43.984
-Never!
-[chuckles]

15:44.068 --> 15:45.069
Good.

15:46.528 --> 15:48.948
Hey, look, I don't mean to be rude,
but I have to ask...

15:49.031 --> 15:50.157
Are you driving home tonight?

15:50.658 --> 15:54.119
Oh, you are so sweet to care. [laughs]

15:54.203 --> 15:55.329
No, I'm--

15:55.829 --> 15:57.081
I'm visiting my son.

15:57.998 --> 16:00.709
In fact, I'm staying at the hotel.

16:00.793 --> 16:02.211
[woman chuckles]

16:12.513 --> 16:14.056
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

16:23.983 --> 16:25.067
Here you go.

16:29.238 --> 16:30.280
Where's the rest?

16:31.657 --> 16:33.534
That is the rest, ma'am.
You gave me a twenty.

16:33.617 --> 16:35.911
I gave you a hundred-dollar bill,
and you know it.

16:35.995 --> 16:36.954
[woman scoffs]

16:37.037 --> 16:38.956
I don't even carry bills
as small as a twenty!

16:39.039 --> 16:39.999
You're a goddamn thief!

16:41.083 --> 16:43.502
Ma'am, I promise you
that's your exact change.

16:43.585 --> 16:44.628
You saw me ring it up.

16:44.712 --> 16:46.380
-Please calm down--
-Don't touch me!

16:46.797 --> 16:48.048
I'm calling the police.

16:51.051 --> 16:51.927
Is there a problem?

16:52.011 --> 16:53.095
Who are you?

16:53.512 --> 16:54.555
The manager.

16:54.638 --> 16:56.515
I heard some commotion
and came over to help.

16:56.932 --> 16:59.268
This bartender here stole money from me.

16:59.351 --> 17:01.478
-I didn't--
-I'm so sorry to hear that, ma'am.

17:02.771 --> 17:04.273
We absolutely can call the police,

17:05.691 --> 17:08.277
and I will go ask Kevin
to pull the security footage right now.

17:08.360 --> 17:10.529
Wait, sorry. Security footage?

17:11.488 --> 17:14.742
Yes, ma'am.
We have hidden cameras behind the bar.

17:15.284 --> 17:17.119
[laughs]

17:17.202 --> 17:18.037
Oh, my gosh.

17:19.413 --> 17:20.706
I am so stupid. [laughs]

17:20.789 --> 17:21.915
[woman] It <i>was </i>a twenty!

17:21.999 --> 17:22.875
I-- [gasps]

17:22.958 --> 17:26.211
I had change from a thing earlier.
[laughs]

17:26.295 --> 17:28.464
I think it's best that you leave that
at the bar, ma'am.

17:31.258 --> 17:33.052
Looks like you've had
a too much to drink.

17:45.606 --> 17:47.066
Can you believe that shit?

17:47.983 --> 17:50.986
I swear, they try to use the police
as their own personal bodyguard.

17:52.613 --> 17:53.489
Security cameras?

17:53.572 --> 17:55.574
[Alana laughs] Yeah, that's bullshit.

17:58.452 --> 18:00.954
Look, if you're trying to get a break
from these folks,

18:01.038 --> 18:03.665
there's this thing
with my friends tonight.

18:04.541 --> 18:05.834
You're welcome to come.

18:06.502 --> 18:09.797
I appreciate it,
but I'm meeting up with a friend tonight.

18:13.383 --> 18:14.426
Some other time.

18:15.552 --> 18:16.386
Yeah.

18:17.471 --> 18:18.430
Yeah.

18:25.479 --> 18:26.522
[sighs]

18:34.238 --> 18:35.072
No!

18:35.656 --> 18:36.990
[hammering on door]

18:37.533 --> 18:38.450
Coming!

18:40.994 --> 18:42.538
-[Kat] Hey.
-[Jenn] Hey.

18:43.163 --> 18:45.374
Outfit for your date tonight,
as requested.

18:45.457 --> 18:46.291
Thanks.

18:46.375 --> 18:48.085
Take it off before you guys, you know--

18:48.168 --> 18:49.044
Gross.

18:49.419 --> 18:50.462
[chuckles]

18:50.546 --> 18:52.714
One second.
I'm just in the middle of something.

18:53.215 --> 18:54.675
What the hell are you doing?

18:55.676 --> 18:57.761
Please don't tell me
you're making your own skin suit.

18:59.388 --> 19:00.472
No!

19:00.556 --> 19:02.349
It's the costume for my long program.

19:02.432 --> 19:04.476
Uh-uh. This is literally
the most terrifying thing

19:04.560 --> 19:06.770
-I've ever seen.
-Look, I don't have a choice,

19:06.854 --> 19:07.688
okay?

19:08.355 --> 19:09.690
My mom drained my bank account.

19:09.773 --> 19:12.151
Now I'm down 700 fucking dollars
that I owe Mandy

19:12.234 --> 19:14.027
for the costume she's having made for me,

19:14.111 --> 19:16.655
and if I can't pay her,
I'm just gonna have to make my own.

19:17.406 --> 19:18.240
Fuck!

19:18.323 --> 19:20.576
Can you go get my seam ripper
from my top dresser drawer?

19:20.659 --> 19:21.743
-Yeah.
-Thank you.

19:22.452 --> 19:24.496
Even if I manage
to make this not look terrible,

19:24.580 --> 19:27.416
I'm still completely screwed
on my whole payment plan.

19:27.791 --> 19:30.419
At this point,
I can't even pay for my ice time anymore.

19:30.502 --> 19:33.297
You have Study Buddies?
You've been holding out.

19:33.380 --> 19:34.798
[sighs]

19:34.882 --> 19:37.968
Just used to take them for a while
to help me focus,

19:38.051 --> 19:39.720
but they made me crazy, so...

19:39.803 --> 19:42.514
All these years,
I thought you were a better skater,

19:42.598 --> 19:45.475
but you've just been using
performance-enhancing drugs.

19:45.559 --> 19:46.768
What else don't I know?

19:48.395 --> 19:50.731
If you need money,
you could get like twenty dollars a pill.

19:50.814 --> 19:52.941
-It's a very lucrative market.
-[material rips]

19:55.527 --> 19:57.654
Jenn, look, I'm drowning here, okay?

19:59.448 --> 20:01.533
This is serious.
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

20:01.617 --> 20:04.328
I know it is, okay?

20:05.412 --> 20:09.541
And I literally have no idea
how you're managing everything.

20:12.878 --> 20:13.837
Okay.

20:13.921 --> 20:15.505
Here. It's not all of it,

20:15.589 --> 20:17.299
but it'll help.

20:17.382 --> 20:18.258
I can't take that.

20:18.342 --> 20:19.301
Take it.

20:19.384 --> 20:22.429
You're like the stressed-out,
high-strung sister I never had.

20:23.722 --> 20:26.475
It's like, what, half the costume, right?

20:26.558 --> 20:29.394
I'm sure Mandy will be fine with that
until you get the rest.

20:29.853 --> 20:30.854
Thank you.

20:32.731 --> 20:34.358
You're the one doing me a favor.

20:34.441 --> 20:37.402
That's like 300 less that I'll blow
at Grayson's Alehouse tonight.

20:37.819 --> 20:42.282
Me, Gabe, and Justin are going there
for College Night.

20:42.366 --> 20:44.534
Not gonna lie, kind of excited!

20:44.618 --> 20:47.120
Now, stop this sad little
arts and craft bullshit!

20:47.204 --> 20:49.164
Go and have fun with Marcus.

20:49.248 --> 20:53.961
You can't let money, stress,
and definitely not Carol ruin your life.

20:56.588 --> 20:57.506
Go!

21:08.141 --> 21:09.726
[sharply inhales]

21:17.067 --> 21:19.361
-[clears throat]
-[engine starts]

21:23.073 --> 21:28.287
<i>♪ Please don't take it so badly ♪</i>

21:30.580 --> 21:32.499
<i>♪ 'Cause you know... ♪</i>

21:32.582 --> 21:33.750
You're my best girl.

21:38.505 --> 21:39.506
[Carol] <i>Get out!</i>

21:39.589 --> 21:40.841
[music stops]

21:41.300 --> 21:43.552
-What?
-I said get out of the car.

21:44.594 --> 21:46.930
Mitch needed to know
what he was getting into.

21:47.014 --> 21:49.891
If you kept dating him
and he saw how crazy you were,

21:49.975 --> 21:51.852
you'd just end up driving him away.

21:51.935 --> 21:54.730
I said get out of this car
before I do something I regret!

22:04.823 --> 22:06.158
[tires screeching]

22:18.128 --> 22:19.796
[Yoka purring]

22:23.425 --> 22:25.010
Argh! I can't believe you!

22:26.345 --> 22:27.596
Little fucker!

22:29.639 --> 22:32.100
-[sighs]
-[cell phone buzzing]

22:32.642 --> 22:34.853
-Hello?
-[Serena]<i> Kat, can you come pick me up</i>

22:34.936 --> 22:35.854
at the rink?

22:35.937 --> 22:38.148
Mom's all mad
because I didn't want her dating Mitch,

22:38.231 --> 22:40.108
and now I'm stuck with no way to get home.

22:40.192 --> 22:41.610
Wait. What? She's dating Mitch?

22:41.693 --> 22:42.569
Kat!

22:43.320 --> 22:44.488
Please just come.

22:44.571 --> 22:45.405
[sighs]

22:45.906 --> 22:47.783
I can't. I'm meeting Marcus.
I'm gonna be late.

22:47.866 --> 22:49.743
<i>My phone's about to die.</i>

22:49.826 --> 22:52.079
Come on.
You'll be, like, five minutes late.

22:52.788 --> 22:53.914
I need your help.

22:54.498 --> 22:55.832
Just be outside, okay?

23:00.587 --> 23:03.840
<i>♪ Honey, let your fire... ♪</i>

23:04.424 --> 23:05.759
[engine blows]

23:06.593 --> 23:07.803
[tires shriek]

23:08.303 --> 23:10.430
You've gotta be fucking kidding me!

23:13.100 --> 23:14.518
No, no, no, no, no!

23:20.190 --> 23:21.191
Fuck!

23:22.692 --> 23:23.527
Fuck!

23:27.739 --> 23:29.574
[cell phone buzzing]

23:29.658 --> 23:31.451
-Yeah?
-[Kat] <i>Hey...</i>

23:32.035 --> 23:32.911
[Reid] Hey, girl.

23:32.994 --> 23:33.829
You look tired.

23:33.912 --> 23:35.789
<i>-...stupid shit car broke down...</i>
-Shut up, Reid.

23:35.872 --> 23:36.957
<i>...out of nowhere.</i>

23:37.040 --> 23:39.042
You look awesome.
You wanna come drive around?

23:39.126 --> 23:40.001
Yeah.

23:40.502 --> 23:43.547
It's fine. Justin's brothers
are gonna give me a ride.

23:45.257 --> 23:46.842
So where are we going?

23:49.386 --> 23:52.472
Hello? Hi.
My car is broken down on Route 75.

23:52.556 --> 23:53.723
I don't know what's wrong.

23:53.807 --> 23:56.268
Can you just tow me
to the nearest repair shop, please?

23:57.477 --> 23:59.187
And then give me a ride
to Pinecrest Lodge?

23:59.271 --> 24:01.481
I'm supposed to meet someone there,
like, now.

24:02.691 --> 24:03.692
Two hours?

24:04.526 --> 24:05.402
Fuck!

24:05.485 --> 24:07.821
No! No, okay, that's fine.
I'll be waiting.

24:12.993 --> 24:13.827
[beeping]

24:14.244 --> 24:16.621
No, no, no, no! Fuck!

24:25.755 --> 24:26.923
No-show, huh?

24:28.383 --> 24:29.217
Hm.

24:29.593 --> 24:32.471
Any chance this friend you're waiting for
is a girlfriend?

24:33.221 --> 24:35.348
To be honest,
I don't know what me and Kat are.

24:35.974 --> 24:36.850
Kat?

24:36.933 --> 24:38.685
Little ice skater chick at Jimmy's?

24:40.437 --> 24:41.521
Oh, come on.

24:41.605 --> 24:43.398
There's nothing wrong
with dating a white girl.

24:43.482 --> 24:44.691
I didn't even say nothing.

24:44.774 --> 24:46.693
Yeah, but I know what you're thinking.

24:46.776 --> 24:48.361
Trust me. I've heard it before.

24:48.737 --> 24:50.614
It's not some big deal. It's just...

24:50.697 --> 24:51.573
all I know.

24:52.032 --> 24:54.034
They were the only girls
I was around growing up.

24:54.618 --> 24:56.203
You do look like the Jack and Jill type.

24:56.703 --> 24:58.163
[both laugh]

24:59.164 --> 25:02.417
So you mean to tell me you didn't meet
any other black girls there?

25:02.501 --> 25:03.335
I did,

25:03.793 --> 25:06.171
but it was always awkward
'cause at every event,

25:06.254 --> 25:08.632
my mom would damn near
make me talk to them,

25:08.715 --> 25:10.634
so it never worked out.

25:11.092 --> 25:11.968
Hm-mm.

25:13.720 --> 25:14.554
[chuckles]

25:14.638 --> 25:16.473
[laughs]

25:16.890 --> 25:18.266
So...

25:18.350 --> 25:20.268
I'm about to go meet my friends.

25:22.312 --> 25:23.855
I think I'm gonna just head home.

25:25.982 --> 25:27.067
You have fun, though.

25:27.609 --> 25:28.610
All right. You too.

25:34.407 --> 25:35.242
Hey, wait.

25:37.994 --> 25:38.828
I'm coming.

25:39.871 --> 25:41.164
<i>♪ I want you to know ♪</i>

25:43.500 --> 25:44.834
<i>♪ I've started to show ♪</i>

25:46.670 --> 25:48.380
<i>♪ It ain't easy ♪</i>

25:50.006 --> 25:51.841
<i>♪ Takin' it slow ♪</i>

25:52.968 --> 25:56.096
<i>♪ So I don't know why it's gotta be... ♪</i>

26:00.600 --> 26:01.518
Justin!

26:01.977 --> 26:04.729
I've had a shit day, and I need
as many drinks as it takes to forget.

26:04.813 --> 26:06.856
[Jenn laughs]
I've been doing that for three months.

26:07.357 --> 26:08.191
Let's go.

26:08.692 --> 26:11.319
<i>♪ We've got to let it go ♪</i>

26:11.403 --> 26:13.905
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪</i>

26:13.989 --> 26:16.074
<i>-♪ And I've got something ♪</i>
<i>-</i>Whiskey? Two whiskeys.

26:16.157 --> 26:17.784
<i>♪ On my mind ♪</i>

26:20.662 --> 26:21.955
<i>♪ We ♪</i>

26:22.038 --> 26:24.249
<i>♪ Have got to let it go ♪</i>

26:24.332 --> 26:26.710
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪</i>

26:27.085 --> 26:28.378
<i>♪ You ♪</i>

26:28.878 --> 26:30.505
<i>♪ I've got somethin' ♪</i>

26:39.931 --> 26:40.807
Hey.

26:40.890 --> 26:42.017
Have you seen Marcus?

26:43.310 --> 26:45.478
He left, like,
I don't know, 45 minutes ago.

26:45.562 --> 26:46.771
-Maybe an hour.
<i>-</i>Shit!

26:47.355 --> 26:48.857
Okay. Can I use your phone?

26:50.817 --> 26:51.860
[Carol] Nice jacket.

26:53.987 --> 26:55.405
Your new mommy buy it for you?

27:01.620 --> 27:04.205
That's a thousand-dollar bottle
of champagne.

27:06.249 --> 27:08.293
You used my savings to buy that.

27:08.376 --> 27:09.586
Limited edition.

27:14.674 --> 27:15.759
You promised.

27:17.719 --> 27:21.014
You promised you'd stay on your meds.
Look at you!

27:21.681 --> 27:24.476
-You're a mess.
-Always with the fucking meds! I'm fine!

27:24.893 --> 27:25.977
I don't have time for this.

27:27.228 --> 27:29.064
[Carol] Don't ignore me!

27:29.147 --> 27:30.565
I am still your mother!

27:31.066 --> 27:31.900
Stop!

27:31.983 --> 27:33.443
Oh, what? What's wrong, Kat?

27:33.526 --> 27:34.819
Am I embarrassing you?

27:34.903 --> 27:37.864
[shouting] Do I embarrass you?
You're gonna wish you were nicer to me.

27:37.947 --> 27:40.158
Calm down, okay? Just-- Just calm down.

27:40.241 --> 27:43.161
No! I will calm down
whenever I'm goddamn ready to calm down!

27:44.996 --> 27:45.955
You'll see!

27:46.706 --> 27:48.833
You'll see you need
to respect your mother!

27:50.210 --> 27:51.961
Me, not that other bitch!

27:57.509 --> 28:00.011
You wanna know what I think of Mandy
and her perfect fucking hair?

28:00.095 --> 28:01.012
[Kat] Stop!

28:01.554 --> 28:03.640
And her perfect
fucking real estate company?

28:04.057 --> 28:07.143
-It's fucking trash! It's all trash!
-[stammering] You're right.

28:07.602 --> 28:10.063
Okay. I'm ungrateful. All right?

28:10.563 --> 28:12.774
I'm sorry. You can keep the money.
Let's get outta here.

28:12.857 --> 28:15.068
No, now you're just saying
what you think I wanna hear.

28:15.151 --> 28:17.862
You think I can't tell the difference
between a lie and the truth!

28:17.946 --> 28:19.197
But I can! I do!

28:19.280 --> 28:21.491
I see everything! I know everything!

28:21.991 --> 28:24.994
Mom, you're having an episode.
We need to leave, okay?

28:25.078 --> 28:26.996
Don't you dare judge me.

28:27.956 --> 28:30.083
'Cause you'll never know what it's like
to get dirty,

28:30.166 --> 28:31.584
clawing your way out of the shit.

28:32.043 --> 28:34.754
How could you?
You don't have the tools to succeed.

28:34.838 --> 28:37.841
You're just a fucking loser
who couldn't get over a little fall!

28:38.675 --> 28:40.009
You're not yourself right now.

28:40.093 --> 28:41.428
At least I'm not you.

28:41.511 --> 28:43.680
You'll never be a champion. Never.

28:44.889 --> 28:46.599
All that glitters isn't gold, Kat,

28:47.308 --> 28:48.601
and you're just a little glitter.

28:48.685 --> 28:50.186
[Mandy] Kat. Carol.

28:52.188 --> 28:53.314
Is everything all right?

28:53.398 --> 28:55.066
Stay out of it.
It's none of your business.

28:55.150 --> 28:56.234
It's okay. It's okay.

28:57.694 --> 28:59.195
Um, I need--

28:59.279 --> 29:00.572
I need to go, okay?

29:00.655 --> 29:01.614
Go.

29:05.243 --> 29:06.494
[panting]

29:06.578 --> 29:09.998
I don't know how you gave birth
to a girl as wonderful as your daughter,

29:10.081 --> 29:11.750
and I don't know what you're on right now,

29:12.500 --> 29:15.545
but if you're gonna mess with Kat,
you'll be messing with me too.

29:15.628 --> 29:18.423
And you do not want to fuck with me!

29:21.134 --> 29:22.927
Could we call a cab for Ms. Baker, please?

29:23.011 --> 29:24.721
-[woman] Yes, absolutely.
-[Mandy] Thank you.

29:34.189 --> 29:36.065
<i>♪ T-t-t-take it back ♪</i>

29:37.567 --> 29:39.360
<i>♪ I should know better ♪</i>

29:41.738 --> 29:43.239
<i>♪ T-t-t-take it back... ♪</i>

29:43.323 --> 29:45.074
Whoo! Yes!

29:45.158 --> 29:47.160
Shake it, Gabe! Shake that ass!

29:48.244 --> 29:50.371
Okay, last shot. Last shot. Here we go.

29:55.418 --> 29:57.128
No chaser all night. You're a champ!

29:57.212 --> 29:58.797
Yeah, everywhere except the ice.

29:58.880 --> 30:00.006
Ssh. Don't tell my parents.

30:00.089 --> 30:02.300
At least you have parents
that actually care about you.

30:02.383 --> 30:03.927
Uh, be careful what you wish for.

30:04.010 --> 30:05.720
It's so much fucking pressure.

30:05.804 --> 30:07.806
I don't know how the hell
I'm gonna keep on skating,

30:07.889 --> 30:09.599
but I have to... for them.

30:10.225 --> 30:11.226
It's really brave.

30:12.101 --> 30:12.936
It's also stupid.

30:13.728 --> 30:16.481
Well, maybe I like to do brave,
stupid shit.

30:26.115 --> 30:28.660
[breathing heavily]

30:31.538 --> 30:33.790
-Do you have a condom?
<i>-</i>Yeah. Glove compartment.

30:34.791 --> 30:35.834
-Ow! My hip.
-Sorry.

30:35.917 --> 30:37.627
Let me just-- One second.

30:41.339 --> 30:42.173
Fuck!

30:42.257 --> 30:44.467
[Jenn laughs] What are you doing?

30:48.304 --> 30:50.056
Really? Ew!

30:51.599 --> 30:52.934
Never mind. It'll still work.

30:53.017 --> 30:54.227
[Jenn] Okay.

30:54.310 --> 30:55.812
[Jenn giggling]

30:58.815 --> 31:01.109
Whoa! What the hell is she doing here?

31:01.776 --> 31:03.695
[Jenn] She's supposed to be on a date.

31:03.778 --> 31:04.779
[Jenn] Ugh!

31:06.155 --> 31:07.991
Something's wrong. [sighs]

31:08.616 --> 31:09.701
I'm gonna go.

31:11.119 --> 31:14.122
Oh... Can we not
mention this mess to anyone?

31:14.205 --> 31:17.208
I never kiss and tell.
And nothing to tell. We're good.

31:17.292 --> 31:18.126
[sighs]

31:18.209 --> 31:20.545
You're calling a Lyft, right?
You definitely can't drive.

31:20.628 --> 31:22.797
I'll probably sleep it off back here.

31:22.881 --> 31:23.840
[Jenn] Okay.

31:31.639 --> 31:32.640
[Jenn grunts]

31:41.524 --> 31:42.442
[clears throat]

31:46.446 --> 31:49.490
-[engine starts]
-[rock music playing]

32:09.594 --> 32:10.803
Kat! Kat!

32:10.887 --> 32:12.513
There you are. Where's Justin and Gabe?

32:12.972 --> 32:16.309
Justin isn't here, but Gabe definitely is.

32:19.020 --> 32:21.564
-Where's Marcus?
-It's a long story.

32:21.648 --> 32:24.525
I'll tell you about it later,
but right now I need your help, okay?

32:24.984 --> 32:26.736
And I need you to keep it
between you and me.

32:27.236 --> 32:30.323
My car broke down,
and the tow truck cost $300.

32:30.406 --> 32:33.076
And it's gonna be $600 on top of that
to get it fixed.

32:33.159 --> 32:36.287
I am sick and tired
of trying to do everything right,

32:36.371 --> 32:38.539
and I will not let my mother
think I failed.

32:39.123 --> 32:41.542
Fuck half the money!
I wanna make all of it.

32:42.251 --> 32:43.628
I'm ready to get dirty.

32:43.711 --> 32:46.422
I'm ready to crawl
and scrape my way out of this shit.

32:46.506 --> 32:48.424
[Jenn] Okay. Calm down there, buddy.

32:48.508 --> 32:49.676
This is not <i>Goodfellas.</i>

32:50.969 --> 32:53.429
Lucky for you,
not only is this College Night,

32:53.513 --> 32:54.681
but it's midterms.

32:54.764 --> 32:55.682
Surge pricing.

32:55.765 --> 32:56.683
Okay.

33:20.748 --> 33:22.125
Looks like Trent Trowley

33:22.208 --> 33:24.627
will be purchasing
the Pabst Blue Ribbon tonight.

33:24.711 --> 33:26.713
[Serena giggling]

33:32.218 --> 33:33.511
It's never gonna work.

33:33.594 --> 33:35.638
<i>-♪ If I leave ♪</i>
-Oh, I love this song.

33:35.722 --> 33:39.058
<i>♪ Here tomorrow ♪</i>

33:40.518 --> 33:41.894
[music stops]

33:41.978 --> 33:43.062
The hell?

33:43.938 --> 33:45.481
Sorry. It's just...

33:47.233 --> 33:49.235
You know when something happens
and it's the worst,

33:49.318 --> 33:52.405
then every time you hear something,
it reminds you how fucked-up things are?

33:55.491 --> 33:56.993
I just hate that song, okay?

33:57.618 --> 33:58.578
Me too.

33:58.661 --> 34:00.371
I'm deleting it from my ears.

34:03.458 --> 34:04.417
[door opens]

34:07.462 --> 34:09.005
Got your Cheetos.

34:10.089 --> 34:11.758
Where's the beer, "Trent?"

34:11.841 --> 34:13.217
ID got taken away.

34:13.968 --> 34:14.844
[chuckling]

34:14.927 --> 34:16.679
-It's not that funny.
-It is.

34:16.763 --> 34:17.805
[laughing]

34:17.889 --> 34:19.891
Hey! How about we see
what Jones and Mac are up to?

34:19.974 --> 34:21.517
-All right, yeah.
-Yeah.

34:21.601 --> 34:23.102
Unless you've got a curfew?

34:23.770 --> 34:25.063
Nope. I'm good.

34:25.646 --> 34:26.689
All righty then.

34:26.773 --> 34:27.899
-We're good!
-Let's roll.

34:27.982 --> 34:28.900
All right!

34:36.908 --> 34:38.493
-[Mitch] Carol?
-[door closes]

34:39.327 --> 34:40.161
Carol?

34:40.995 --> 34:41.829
Um...

34:41.913 --> 34:44.123
You know your front door is wide open?

34:44.207 --> 34:46.209
[continues scrubbing]

34:48.169 --> 34:49.629
I've been trying to call you.

34:54.675 --> 34:56.427
-Carol?
-You don't understand.

34:56.511 --> 34:58.471
If the house isn't clean,
my girls won't come home.

34:58.554 --> 35:00.723
They'll need a clean house,
or they'll get sick.

35:00.807 --> 35:03.392
And if they get sick,
I'll never be able to forgive myself.

35:10.316 --> 35:11.984
[Mitch] Hey, hey, hey.

35:12.068 --> 35:13.903
-[Carol struggles]
-[Mitch] Sh-sh.

35:15.822 --> 35:17.615
Mandy's a better mom than me.

35:20.368 --> 35:22.036
And now Serena hates me too.

35:23.913 --> 35:25.540
And I need to clean the fucking floor.

35:27.416 --> 35:29.085
I'll help you clean.

35:29.669 --> 35:30.795
[Mitch] Can I do that?

35:33.297 --> 35:34.132
Just...

35:35.258 --> 35:36.509
tell me where it's dirty.

35:40.847 --> 35:41.806
Okay.

35:43.349 --> 35:45.184
[scrubbing]

35:47.228 --> 35:48.396
What Serena said...

35:53.234 --> 35:54.610
I'm bipolar.

35:55.027 --> 35:57.321
But when I take my meds, I'm all flat.

35:57.405 --> 35:58.906
And I don't wanna be a bad mom.

36:00.616 --> 36:02.451
Mandy's a better mom than me.

36:02.535 --> 36:04.579
And now Serena hates me too.

36:07.123 --> 36:08.958
But I have to wait up for Serena.

36:09.041 --> 36:11.043
What if I keep cleaning and...

36:12.211 --> 36:13.087
you get some sleep?

36:13.171 --> 36:15.089
I can't. Not till Serena gets home.

36:15.756 --> 36:17.049
I'll wait up for Serena.

36:18.676 --> 36:19.719
You should rest.

36:23.055 --> 36:24.098
Okay.

36:41.490 --> 36:42.658
Ugh!

36:44.118 --> 36:46.078
What is your car doing on my golf course?

36:47.788 --> 36:49.248
[Justin] What's... [sighs]

36:50.291 --> 36:51.542
[Justin] Well...

36:51.626 --> 36:55.213
that's the 12th tee, right?
So I was probably scared of hooking it.

36:55.296 --> 36:57.131
This some kinda joke to you?

36:57.215 --> 36:58.549
No! Twelfth's a killer.

36:59.133 --> 37:01.719
Three hundred yards, damn sand trap.

37:05.223 --> 37:07.391
Okay, yeah, I'll pay for the damage
to the greens, okay?

37:08.476 --> 37:11.229
You think I give a shit
about the goddamn greens?

37:11.604 --> 37:14.023
You got drunk,
and you got behind the wheel of a car!

37:14.106 --> 37:17.193
I was a block away from the bar, Dad.
I was taking a shortcut.

37:17.693 --> 37:21.447
You got drunk,
and you got behind the wheel of a car.

37:25.701 --> 37:26.619
Fuck.

37:28.329 --> 37:29.163
[sighs]

37:29.247 --> 37:30.748
You're right, Dad. That was...

37:32.875 --> 37:34.877
That was stupid. I wasn't thinking about--

37:34.961 --> 37:37.505
I can't do this again, Justin. I can't.

37:38.464 --> 37:39.882
I can't lose you this way, too.

37:39.966 --> 37:41.842
Dad, you won't. Okay?

37:45.930 --> 37:47.223
This won't happen again.

37:47.890 --> 37:48.975
I promise.

37:49.850 --> 37:51.936
I'm sorry you found out the way you did.

37:52.645 --> 37:53.604
It's okay.

37:54.772 --> 37:56.524
And I will always love your mother.

37:57.942 --> 37:59.527
I miss her like hell.

38:01.779 --> 38:02.613
Yeah.

38:08.160 --> 38:09.704
I blame myself for this.

38:11.956 --> 38:13.082
Your behavior.

38:14.000 --> 38:15.001
I've coddled you.

38:16.085 --> 38:19.088
I've given you too much,
trying to fill a void your mother left.

38:20.881 --> 38:22.967
But I can't do this anymore, Justin.

38:23.050 --> 38:24.427
This is your final warning.

38:25.136 --> 38:26.220
One more fuck-up,

38:27.138 --> 38:28.139
one more,

38:28.723 --> 38:30.016
-and I'm finished.
-Dad...

38:38.024 --> 38:39.233
[door opens]

38:44.155 --> 38:45.364
[door closes]

39:03.007 --> 39:04.050
Where's my mom?

39:08.471 --> 39:10.139
[Serena] <i>Daddy! Daddy, no!</i>

39:10.222 --> 39:11.807
Daddy, wait! [crying]

39:12.350 --> 39:15.603
Leave, you piece of shit!<i> </i>Get out of here!

39:15.686 --> 39:17.063
We don't need you!

39:19.148 --> 39:21.734
And your daughter's
not even gonna remember your name!

39:21.817 --> 39:23.778
<i>♪ I can't change ♪</i>

39:25.404 --> 39:28.783
<i>♪ Won't you fly high ♪</i>

39:28.866 --> 39:32.078
<i>♪ Free bird, yeah... ♪</i>

39:36.999 --> 39:38.584
[sobbing]

39:43.964 --> 39:44.924
So...

39:47.051 --> 39:48.177
when are you leaving?

39:48.761 --> 39:50.721
-Serena, I--
-You know she's sick.

39:52.306 --> 39:54.809
When are you leaving?

39:55.893 --> 39:57.311
I'm not going anywhere.

40:00.272 --> 40:01.107
Here...

40:05.820 --> 40:07.530
I think this is the one you liked.

40:17.957 --> 40:19.708
[sobbing]

40:31.846 --> 40:33.597
[panting]

40:33.681 --> 40:36.684
[Serena sobbing]

40:49.780 --> 40:51.782
[beeping]

40:55.035 --> 40:57.037
[line ringing]

40:59.248 --> 41:00.583
This is Carol Baker...

41:01.750 --> 41:03.335
calling for Dr. Kessler.

41:06.088 --> 41:07.631
I want to check myself in.

41:09.091 --> 41:10.176
I need help.

41:14.305 --> 41:15.931
[cell phone buzzing]

41:28.444 --> 41:30.571
Hey. Yo, Marcus! You've gotta meet my mom.

41:30.654 --> 41:33.240
Marcus and I met yesterday, didn't we?

41:33.324 --> 41:35.659
Brent told me you're the fastest guy
on the team now.

41:38.078 --> 41:40.080
Knocked my son right out of the top spot.

41:40.664 --> 41:42.208
Not an easy task.

41:44.668 --> 41:47.338
She's gotta catch a five o'clock flight,
but glad you guys could meet.

41:47.421 --> 41:48.589
Catch you later, dude.

41:57.556 --> 41:59.558
[country music playing]

42:04.355 --> 42:05.439
Kat Baker.

42:06.148 --> 42:08.400
-[James] Nice you could join us.
-Thanks for having me.

42:08.943 --> 42:10.277
Thank you for coming.

42:11.529 --> 42:13.781
Here's the money for the costumes.

42:14.615 --> 42:16.784
Seven hundred dollars. It's all there.

42:17.284 --> 42:20.496
Oh, thank you, sweetie, but you know
you really didn't have to do that.

42:21.121 --> 42:22.581
[James] I know why she did it.

42:22.665 --> 42:24.667
I'm the same way. Never liked a handout.

42:24.750 --> 42:28.128
And thank you, by the way,
for being such a good example with Justin.

42:28.212 --> 42:30.714
He certainly needs all the help
he can get right now.

42:33.676 --> 42:35.052
Seven hundred?

42:36.345 --> 42:37.680
Those costumes are five grand!

42:39.056 --> 42:41.767
I know what it's like to be a proud girl
with no money.

42:45.354 --> 42:46.188
[Kat] Marcus?

42:46.689 --> 42:47.523
I'm--

42:47.606 --> 42:48.607
I'm so sorry.

42:48.691 --> 42:50.484
Yeah, me too.

42:51.902 --> 42:54.029
[Marcus clears throat] Mr. Davis?

42:56.532 --> 42:57.616
Excellent.

43:00.244 --> 43:01.745
What was that all about?

43:01.829 --> 43:02.955
Nothing.

43:04.415 --> 43:05.708
What happened to you?

43:08.085 --> 43:09.295
Car trouble.

43:10.629 --> 43:11.755
Yeah.

43:11.839 --> 43:12.673
Me too.

43:13.632 --> 43:16.343
<i>♪ Gotta see it! Gotta see it! ♪</i>

43:22.099 --> 43:23.892
<i>♪ The tip of your tongue ♪</i>

43:23.976 --> 43:26.312
<i>♪ Like candy, I crave ya ♪</i>

43:34.278 --> 43:36.572
<i>♪ Wanted to believe it ♪</i>

43:36.655 --> 43:39.575
<i>♪ I need your real love ♪</i>

43:39.658 --> 43:41.869
<i>♪ I want more ♪</i>

43:41.952 --> 43:47.082
<i>♪ I need that real touch I adore</i> ♪

43:47.166 --> 43:51.712
<i>♪ Give me a reason</i>
<i>I can't see you anymore ♪</i>

43:51.795 --> 43:53.547
<i>♪ I want more ♪</i>

43:53.631 --> 43:57.718
<i>♪ I want more ♪</i>

44:01.138 --> 44:03.724
<i>♪ I want more ♪</i>

44:06.226 --> 44:07.728
<i>♪ I want it ♪</i>

44:19.448 --> 44:23.577
<i>♪ I want it and I need it</i> ♪

44:24.411 --> 44:27.081
<i>♪ Gotta see it! Gotta see it! ♪</i>
